Subject: Greece in the Junior Eurovision Song Contest 2008 
To: Noah
Content:
Greece selected its Junior Eurovision Song Contest 2008 entry by a national final held on 27 September 2008. It was hosted by Yiorgos Amyras and Renia Tsitsibikou. The winner was Niki Giannoutsou with "Kapia Nichta" who went on to represent Greece in the Junior Eurovision Song Contest 2008 on 22 November 2008. [1] "Selection for Cyprus", the Greek national final, selected its entrant for 2008. At Junior Eurovision, Greece performed in the fifth position and placed fourteenth overall. [2]
